        "observed_type": "list_item",
        "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
        "text": "Proof. 1. L(U,V) is clearly nonempty: the zero mapping O is in it. Theorem 4.2.9 shows that L(U, V) is closed under addition and multiplication by scalars. The vector space axioms for L(U,V) follow from the corresponding ones in V for every x in y = T (x). In particular, the zero element is the zero mapping O, and the element —T is the mapping (- 1) T.",
        "bbox": [
          0.11894272673289191,
          0.6671511630165573,
          0.8788546217341454,
          0.7572674412593317
        ],
        "order": 14
